## Common Operations

### Restart the Service

```bash
# Kubernetes
kubectl rollout restart deployment/{{ system_name | lower | replace(' ', '-') }} -n production

# Docker Compose
docker compose restart {{ system_name | lower | replace(' ', '-') }}
```

**When to do this:** [Specific symptoms that warrant a restart]
**Expected outcome:** Service recovers within [N] seconds. Check [metric] in [dashboard].

### Scale Up

```bash
# Kubernetes — increase replica count
kubectl scale deployment/{{ system_name | lower | replace(' ', '-') }} --replicas=N -n production
```

**When to do this:** [Symptom: e.g., p99 latency sustained above 500ms for >5 minutes]
**Expected outcome:** [What improves and on what timescale]

### Flush Cache

```bash
# Redis flush (CAUTION: clears all keys — confirm with team lead first)
redis-cli -h [redis-host] FLUSHDB
```

**When to do this:** [Specific stale-cache symptom]
**Impact:** [Performance hit immediately after flush, expected recovery time]

